//semantic 
every tag in html has an opening and a closing tag
opening
<>
closing
</>

DOCTYPE>>Tells the browser that this document is html document
its the only tag that is outside html tags

html>>contains data content of the website

head>> contains meta tags,links to other sources(js,css,libraries,framework,fonts)
title>> title of the page  
body>>component of the page
footer

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-with,initial-scale=1.0">
        <title>Document</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        //tags in html
        the most common used tags in html are the following:(h,p,b,i.em,strong,article
        section,a,br,hr,div,)
        /head tag
        outlines the important component of a particular website
        these are things like names of organisations,particular values,product,etc
        a particular well structured heading tag should not be less than three word and should not exceed six words
        h1 is the most importsnt heading tag
        
        heading tags are arranged and follow a hierachial order
        the first tag is h1 while the last tag is h6
        the first heading tag is the largest in font size while the last tag is the smallest in size
        <h1>hello world</h1>
        <h2>hello world</h2>
        <h3>hello world again</h3>
        <h4>how are you</h4>
        <h5>hello am coding</h5>
        <h6>hello am coding again</h6>

        /paragraph tag
        refers to the informsation or content that is describing
        a particular heading,giving us more information regarding it
        <h1>Eustus muchina</h1>
        <p> i am a software engineer with a degreein computer science and i envission to become the most proficient
            programmer to ever walk on planet earth,let alone have skills but the hte mindset of a genious
        </p>
        /article tag
        article tag>> contains a detailed explanation to a particular context>> it superceeds the paragraph tag
        it is commonly used in blogs,newsletters to offer details
    </body>
</html>





